:{"href":"/us/pl/97/113/tVI"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–113, title VI","children":[],"tail":", §§ 601(e)(1), 602, 603, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1981-12-29"},"text":"Dec. 29, 1981","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/95/1542"},"text":"95 Stat. 1542","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/83/tXI/s1101"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–83, title XI, § 1101","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1985-08-08"},"text":"Aug. 8, 1985","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/99/272"},"text":"99 Stat. 272","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/399/tXIII/s1301"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–399, title XIII, § 1301","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1986-08-27"},"text":"Aug. 27, 1986","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/100/897"},"text":"100 Stat. 897","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/565/s1"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–565, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1992-10-28"},"text":"Oct. 28, 1992","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/106/4265"},"text":"106 Stat. 4265","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/30/s1"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–30, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1999-05-21"},"text":"May 21, 1999","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/113/55"},"text":"113 Stat. 55","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id8fca3a82-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id8fca3a83-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id8fca3a84-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This chapter, referred to in subsecs. (a) to (c), was in the original “this Act”, meaning ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/87/293"},"text":"Pub. L. 87–293","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1961-09-22"},"text":"Sept. 22, 1961","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/75/612"},"text":"75 Stat. 612","children":[],"tail":", known as the Peace Corps Act. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s2501"},"text":"section 2501 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id8fca3a85-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1999—Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/30"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–30","children":[],"tail":" amended subsec. (b) generally. Prior to amendment, subsec. (b) read as follows: “There are authorized to be appropriated to carry out the purposes of this chapter $218,146,000 for fiscal year 1993, which are authorized to remain available until "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-09-30"},"text":"September 30, 1994","children":[],"tail":".”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1992—Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/565"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–565","children":[],"tail":" amended subsec. (b) generally. Prior to amendment, subsec. (b) read as follows: “There are authorized to be appropriated to carry out the purposes of this chapter $130,000,000 for the fiscal year 1986 and $137,200,000 for the fiscal year 1987.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1986—Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/399"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–399","children":[],"tail":" in amending subsec. (b) generally, substituted provision authorizing appropriations of $130,000,000 for fiscal year 1986 and $137,200,000 for fiscal year 1987 for provision authorizing appropriations of $130,000,000 for fiscal years 1986 and 1987, providing that unobligated balances continue to be made available for the general purposes for which appropriated, and prohibiting the use of funds to carry out this chapter for the Volunteers to America Program or any similar program involving the service or training of foreign nationals in the United States."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1985—Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/83"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–83","children":[],"tail":" substituted provisions authorizing appropriations of $130,000,000 for fiscal years 1986 and 1987 for provisions authorizing appropriations of not to exceed $105,000,000 for fiscal years 1982 and 1983, and struck out provisos limiting use of funds in fiscal year 1967, and limiting contracts and agreements for research."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1981—Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/113/s602/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–113, § 602(a)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “the fiscal year 1982 not to exceed $105,000,000 and for the fiscal year 1983 not to exceed $105,000,000” for “fiscal year 1981 not to exceed $118,000,000”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/113/s602/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–113, § 602(b)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “each fiscal year” for “fiscal year 1981”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (d). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/113/s601/e/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–113, § 601(e)(1)","children":[],"tail":", redesignated subsec. (g) as (d) and struck out former subsec. (d) which provided for rectification of imbalance in readjustment allowance for the period "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1961-03-01"},"text":"Mar. 1, 1961","children":[],"tail":", to "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1973-02-28"},"text":"Feb. 28, 1973","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (e). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/113/s601/e/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–113, § 601(e)(1)","children":[],"tail":", struck out subsec. (e) which related to waiver of claims resulting from erroneous payments to volunteers who terminated their volunteer service between "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1961-03-01"},"text":"Mar. 1, 1961","children":[],"tail":", and "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1973-02-28"},"text":"Feb. 28, 1973","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (f). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/113/s601/e/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–113, § 601(e)(1)","children":[],"tail":", struck out subsec. (f) which related to relief from liability for improper payment of readjustment allowances made to volunteers between "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1961-03-01"},"text":"Mar. 1, 1961","children":[],"tail":", and "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1973-02-28"},"text":"Feb. 28, 1973","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (g). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/113/s601/e/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–113, § 601(e)(1)","children":[],"tail":", redesignated subsec. (g) as (d)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (h). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/113/s603"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–113, § 603","children":[],"tail":", added subsec. (h)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1980—Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/533/s601/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–533, § 601(a)","children":[],"tail":", substituted appropriations authorization of $118,000,000 for fiscal year 1981 for such authorization of $105,404,000 for fiscal year 1980."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/533/s601/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–533, § 601(b)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “1981” for “1980”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1979—Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/53/s301/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–53, § 301(1)","children":[],"tail":", substituted provisions authorizing to be appropriated for fiscal year 1980 not to exceed $105,404,000, for provisions authorizing to be appropriated for fiscal year 1978 not to exceed $86,544,000, and for fiscal year 1979 not to exceed $112,424,000, and setting forth availability of funds for the United Nations contributions by the Corps."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/53/s301/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–53, § 301(2)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “1980” for “1978, $1,069,000, and for fiscal year 1979”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1978—Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/331/s3/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–331, § 3(1)","children":[],"tail":", substituted provisions authorizing to be appropriated for fiscal year 1978 not to exceed $86,544,000 and for fiscal year 1979 not to exceed $112,424,000 and limitation with respect to volunteer program, for provisions authorizing to be appropriated for fiscal year 1978 not to exceed $82,900,000."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/331/s3/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–331, § 3(2)","children":[],"tail":", inserted provisions increasing 1978 appropriation from $1,000,000 to $1,069,000, and provisions authorizing to be appropriated such sums as necessary for fiscal year